Peter Obi, the former governor of Anambra State, has prophesied that in the next 2023 general elections, he will emerge as a consensus candidate for the entire country. On Saturday, the presidential hopeful told journalists at his Onitsha GRA mansion that he had substantial backing from all major parties in the country. He stated that he would ensure adequate consultations and that the person best suited to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari will be chosen in the end. Also Read: I Don’t Know Whether There Will Be 2023 Election Yet – Pastor Adeboye Says “They didn’t say consensus is from a particular section; it might be consensus for Nigeria, and as we are going round, we shall be discussing everything. “You never know I might be the consensus candidate. I agree we shall be talking to each other and in the end, we shall find out who is the best for the job,” he said. Obi urged Nigerians to investigate and interrogate aspirants to uncover their previous achievements and failures, stressing that his antecedents will speak favourably for him.